find_next_wave_value

Description: 
Find next waveform value

Syntax: 
find_next_wave_value  [-wave <arg>] [-radix <arg>] [-match <arg>] [-time <arg>]
                      [-quiet] [-verbose] [<pattern>]

Usage: 
  Name         Description
  ------------------------
  [-wave]      the wave object to search for value
  [-radix]     radix specifies the radix to use for the value pattern. Allowed
               values are: dec, bin, oct,hex, unsigned
  [-match]     match specifies the match location to use for the value 
               pattern. Allowed values are: exact, beginning, end
  [-time]      starting time. The defaul time unit is ns.
  [-quiet]     Ignore command errors
  [-verbose]   Suspend message limits during command execution
  [<pattern>]  value pattern to be search

Categories: 
Waveform

